---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="eyebrow">About</div>
    <h1>Building AI systems that work in practice.</h1>
    <p class="hero-lede">
      I'm Hankyeol Kyung, an AI/agent engineer based in Seoul. I care about the layer where
      models meet memory, runtime constraints, and real human workflows.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">How I think about systems</span>
    <p>
      <strong>Harness over model.</strong> In applied agent work, capability depends less on the
      model than on the harness around it: tool integration, runtime environments, context
      packaging, session handling, and evaluation loops.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Interface bridges over substrate.</strong> Sometimes the right move is not replacing
      the backend, but changing the surface on top of it. Powerful systems fail if the entry
      point is awkward.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Structured control over prompting.</strong> Agents are not just something you prompt.
      They are sessions and runtime objects that can be resumed, steered, inspected, and automated.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Memory as both knowledge and runtime.</strong> Agent memory is not only a storage
      problem. It is also a runtime UX problem: continuity, correctness, and how context survives
      over time.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">Principles</span>
    <ul>
      <li>Ship over polish.</li>
      <li>Good infrastructure disappears into the workflow.</li>
      <li>Agents should extend how you think, not replace it.</li>
      <li>The best systems feel collaborative, not theatrical.</li>
      <li>Private knowledge layer upstream, curated public layer downstream.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">Contact</span>
    <p>
      The easiest public surfaces are <a href="https://github.com/keenranger">GitHub</a> and
      <a href="https://x.com/hankyeolkyung">X</a>. If you want the sharper version of what I'm thinking,
      <a href="/direction">Direction</a> is the best place to start.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
